AWS CDK Infrastructure — Custodian AI Army (ARCHIVED)
======================================================

This file documents the AWS CDK infrastructure that was set up and tested but
ultimately removed in favor of a simpler local-only setup using SQLite
(custodian.db). Keep this as a reference if you want to migrate back to AWS.

Account: 394820919743
Region:  us-east-1

Architecture
------------

    Vercel (React)  --/api/*-->  EC2 t3.micro (FastAPI)  --TCP:5432-->  RDS PostgreSQL

Stacks (created via infra/ CDK):

  Stack              | Service            | Cost           | Free Tier
  -------------------|--------------------|----------------|-----------------------
  CustodianVpc       | VPC + subnets      | $0/mo          | Always free
  CustodianRds       | PostgreSQL 16      | ~$17/mo yr 2+  | db.t3.micro (12 mo)
  CustodianBackend   | EC2 t3.micro       | ~$8/mo yr 2+   | t3.micro (12 mo)

Files that were in infra/ (for reference):

  infra/app.py                 # CDK entry point — wires VPC -> RDS -> Backend
  infra/cdk.json               # CDK config ("app": ".venv\\Scripts\\python.exe app.py")
  infra/requirements.txt       # aws-cdk-lib, constructs, boto3
  infra/README.md              # Full deploy + lifecycle guide (see summary below)
  infra/stacks/vpc_stack.py    # VPC: 2 AZs, public + isolated subnets, 0 NAT gateways
  infra/stacks/rds_stack.py    # RDS: PostgreSQL 16, db.t3.micro, 20GB gp3, backup=1d
  infra/stacks/backend_stack.py# EC2: t3.micro, Amazon Linux 2023, systemd, UserData

Prerequisites (if re-deploying)
-------------------------------
  1. Install AWS CLI: winget install Amazon.AWSCLI
  2. Configure: aws configure (Access Key ID, Secret Key, us-east-1)
  3. Install CDK: npm install -g aws-cdk
  4. Bootstrap: cdk bootstrap aws://394820919743/us-east-1

Deploy (if re-deploying)
------------------------
  cdk deploy --all --require-approval never ^
    -c db_password=<password> ^
    -c anthropic_key=sk-ant-... ^
    -c gemini_key=AI... ^
    -c jwt_secret=<hex> ^
    -c github_url=https://github.com/Tushar1224/CustodianAIArmy.git

Known issues from deploy attempt (2026-06-21):
  - RDS backup_retention must be 1 day (free tier max, not 7)
  - SG descriptions must be ASCII only (no em dashes/en dashes)
  - Cross-stack dependency cycle: CfnSecurityGroupIngress owned by BackendStack
    to avoid RDS SG -> Backend SG -> RDS cycle
  - CDK must use .venv Python: set "app" to ".venv\\Scripts\\python.exe app.py"

Lifecycle (if re-deployed)
--------------------------
  | Scenario                     | Action                               | Downtime  |
  |------------------------------|--------------------------------------|-----------|
  | Change backend code          | SSH -> git pull -> systemctl restart  | 2-5s      |
  | Change API keys              | Edit .env -> systemctl restart        | 2-5s      |
  | Change EC2 type/storage      | Edit CDK -> cdk deploy                | 2-3 min   |
  | Change RDS storage           | Edit CDK -> cdk deploy                | None      |
  | Full destroy                 | cdk destroy -> cdk destroy -> destroy | Permanent |

  Connect: aws ssm start-session --target <InstanceId>
  View logs: sudo journalctl -u custodian -f

Outputs (from successful deploy)
---------------------------------
  BackendIp   = EC2 public IP (set in Vercel vercel.json rewrites)
  BackendUrl  = http://<IP>:8000
  InstanceId  = EC2 instance ID (for SSM)
  DbEndpoint  = RDS hostname

Local SQLite Setup (current)
-----------------------------
  Database file: custodian.db (auto-created in project root)
  No AWS services needed. Backend uses SQLite via sqlite3.
  DB is ephemeral between restarts if using in-memory; otherwise persists.
